==English==

===Etymology===
Representing a [[Cockney]] pronunciation of "[[God]] [[blind]] [[me]]!"; in [[medieval]] times, people would curse using [[contractions]] rather than breaking the [[w:Ten commandments|third commandment]] (Do not use the Lord's name in [[vain]] [[oath]]s).  Compare [[strewth]], [[zounds]], [['sblood]].

===Alternative forms===
* [[blimey]]
* [[gor blimey!]]

===Interjection===
'''gorblimey!'''
#(''British'') Expressing [[surprise]], [[anger]], etc.

